fiftyone.mobile.detection
Class Factory

java.lang.Object
  fiftyone.mobile.detection.Factory

public class Factory
extends Object

Class used to create a Provider if you have a premium license agreement. The class will automatically update the Provider that is being used.

Version:
2.2.9.1
Author:
51Degrees.mobi

Parameters:

getProvider

public Provider getProvider()
Returns the active provider with the most current data available. Requires Premium device data to return anything other than embedded data. The instance returned should not be stored when updates are enabled to ensure the most recent data is always being used.

Returns:
The latest 51Degrees.mobi provider.

update

public boolean update()
Uses the licence key given to the factory in initialize method to perform a device data update, writing the data to the file system and filling providers from this factory instance with it.

Returns:
true for a successful update. False can indicate that data was unavailable, no licence key was supplied, corrupt, older than the current data or not enough memory was available. In that case the current data is used.

update

public boolean update(String licenceKey)
Uses the given license key to perform a device data update, writing the data to the file system and filling providers from this factory instance with it.

Parameters:
licenceKey - the licence key to submit to the server
Returns:
true for a successful update. False can indicate that data was unavailable, corrupt, older than the current data or not enough memory was available. In that case the current data is used.
